---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { withBase } from "../config.mjs";
import { app } from "../data/app.mjs";

const updated = "June 23, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  path="/terms/"
  description="KaiZenly+ terms of use. Plain-English terms covering your licence, your responsibilities, and the as-is nature of this free privacy-first Android app for habits, focus & journaling."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="display-lg" style="margin-top:10px">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="lede" style="margin-top:16px">
        These terms explain the simple agreement between you and KaiZenly+ when you install and use
        the app. They are written in plain English on purpose — there is nothing hidden here.
      </p>

      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:40px">
        <h2 class="display-sm serif">1. Accepting these terms</h2>
        <p>
          By installing or using KaiZenly+, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do
          not use the app. KaiZenly+ is made by one solo student developer based in Pakistan, not a
          company.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">2. Your licence to use the app</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ is <strong>proprietary, closed-source software</strong> — the source code is
          private and all rights are reserved. You are granted a personal, non-exclusive,
          non-transferable licence to install and use the app on devices you own or control, for
          your own self-improvement. You may not copy, sell, rent, decompile, reverse-engineer, or
          redistribute the app or any part of it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">3. The app is provided “as is”</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ is offered <strong>free and as is</strong>, without warranties of any kind. While
          it is built carefully, it cannot be guaranteed to be error-free or available at all times.
          To the maximum extent allowed by law, the developer is not liable for any loss of data,
          loss of profit, or other damages arising from your use of the app.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">4. Your data and backups are your responsibility</h2>
        <p>
          Your data lives on your device in an <strong>encrypted</strong> database, and your backups
          are <strong>encrypted</strong> too. A backup is unlocked only by a password you choose —
          that password is <strong>never stored and cannot be recovered</strong> by the app. If you
          lose it, your backup cannot be opened by anyone, including the developer. Please keep your
          backup password somewhere safe.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">5. Permissions and focus features</h2>
        <p>
          Some features — mainly Focus / Zen Shield — need device permissions to work. The app does
          <strong>not</strong> have “zero permissions”; each permission it asks for is explained
          line-by-line on the <a href={withBase("/permissions/")}>Permissions page</a>. You are in
          control of which features you enable.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">6. Not medical or professional advice</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ is a focus and habit tool. It is <strong>not</strong> a medical device and does
          not provide medical, therapy, or mental-health treatment. If you need professional help,
          please reach out to a qualified professional.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">7. Price and future features</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ is fully free today (version {app.version}) with every feature included. If
          server, backend, or AI features are ever added in the future, some of those <em>may</em>
          become paid — but nothing is paid today, and any change would be announced first.
        </p>

        <h2 class=”display-sm serif”>8. Age requirement</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ is a general self-improvement tool. It is not directed at children under 13
          years of age. By using the app, you confirm that you are at least 13 years old, or that
          a parent or guardian has reviewed and agreed to these terms on your behalf if you are
          younger than the age of majority in your jurisdiction. Because the developer collects no
          personal data, no special handling of minors' data is required beyond this confirmation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">9. Export compliance</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to comply with all applicable export and re-export laws and regulations. You
          may not download or use KaiZenly+ in violation of any applicable export restrictions,
          embargoes, or sanctions.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">10. Governing law and dispute resolution</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of Pakistan, where the developer is based, without
          regard to conflict-of-law rules. Any dispute arising out of or relating to these terms or
          the app shall first be attempted to be resolved through good-faith negotiation. If
          negotiation fails, the parties agree to resolve the dispute through the courts of
          Pakistan, unless applicable local law requires otherwise in your jurisdiction.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">11. Severability</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these terms is found to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable by a
          court of competent jurisdiction, that provision will be modified to the minimum extent
          necessary to make it enforceable, or severed if modification is not possible. The
          remaining provisions continue in full force and effect.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">12. Entire agreement</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms &amp; Conditions, together with the{" "}
          <a href={withBase("/privacy-policy/")}>Privacy Policy</a>, constitute the entire
          agreement between you and the developer regarding KaiZenly+. They supersede any prior
          agreements, understandings, or representations relating to the app.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">13. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          These terms may be updated as the app evolves. The "last updated" date below always shows
          the current version. Continuing to use the app after a change means you accept the updated
          terms. Material changes will be noted on the <a href={withBase("/about/")}>About</a> page.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">14. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For any questions about these terms, email the developer at{" "}
          <a href="mailto:kaizenlyplus@gmail.com">kaizenlyplus@gmail.com</a>.
          KaiZenly+ is maintained by a solo student developer in Pakistan who will respond as
          promptly as possible.
        </p>

        <p class="muted" style="margin-top:32px;font-size:0.88rem">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:32px">
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={withBase("/privacy-policy/")}>Privacy Policy</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={withBase("/data-safety/")}>Data Safety →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
